<DOC><DOCNO> DOE2-41-0230 </DOCNO><TEXT>Heat transfer characteristics of the gas flow within converging annularchannel were investigated through experimental and numerical procedures.The k-{epsilon} turbulence model was found to give an adequate predictionof the measured streamwise variation of the Nusselt number in the widerange of the heating rate. Calculated profiles of the turbulent energyand average streamwise velocity within the converging section suggestthat the process of the flow laminarization is substantially differentfrom those of the converging plane flow.</TEXT></DOC>